oxshall</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FE002501%2F1"><gtr:id>98AA603B-80B9-4E42-A728-925D453F7023</gtr:id><gtr:title>Civil Society, Kinship and Conflict: Community (Re)construction and Reconciliation in the Andean Highlands of Ayacucho, Peru</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/E002501/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This Fellowship has several aims: &lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>To revise the Fellow?s doctoral thesis and submit the manuscript for publication as a monograph;&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To disseminate this doctoral research;&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To set up a further, comparative research project amongst five communities in the Andean highlands on the themes, ?Civil Society, Kinship and Community?;&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To organise and conduct an interdisciplinary workshop on ?Civil Society, Kinship, and Community? and publish the papers in an edited collection, later;&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To publish an article based on the Fellow?s recent experience as member of a delegation on mining and development in Peru, organised by the Peru Support Group.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>The new research project will expand on the main argument of the Fellow?s doctoral thesis that kinship relations, which are intrinsically conflicted, shaped how political violence in Peru was performed and the ways local people and intervening outside agencies promoted (re)construction, ?reconciliation? and healing processes within community in a contemporary context. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>Possible research questions include: &lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>How far do kinship relations challenge/promote ?successful? community (re)construction, civil society relations and democracy (cf. Putnam 1993)?&lt;br />&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>How might ?fictive? kin relations amongst Andean people who converted to Evangelicalism during the political violence, impact on existing kinship practices in the Andes?&lt;/li>
